            <p>In this example we are processing a MSAB with three lines and currently the third line is the one being processed. Depending of the symbol, the sequence can be split into at most three streams. The first stream corresponds to the DNA bases and gaps. The second stream represents the extra symbols (Nâ€™s and nâ€™s). The last stream is used to process the upper/lower case information. All these streams are encoded using FCM and arithmetic coding.</p>
